Quote: We were at home again beside the stream/ Fringed with tall berry bushes, white and red./ `Don't touch them: they are poisonous,' I said./ ... And as you stooped I saw the berries gleam./ `Don't you remember? We called them Dead man's Bread!'
Notes: 1916 Mansfield in 1923 Poems 47(To L.H.B. (1894-1915)
